# Sāba

[![NPM version](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/saba.svg?style=flat-square)](https://npmjs.com/package/saba) [![NPM downloads](https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/saba.svg?style=flat-square)](https://npmjs.com/package/saba) [![Build Status](https://img.shields.io/circleci/project/egoist/saba/master.svg?style=flat-square)](https://circleci.com/gh/egoist/saba)

## Install

```bash
$ npm install --save saba
```

## Usage

```js
const {saba, send} = require('saba')

const app = saba((req, res) => {
  if (req.url === '/404') {
    return sned(res, 'not found', 404)
  }
  send(res, 'hello world')
})

app.listen(3000)
```

### Handle Error

```js
const handleError = fn => {
  return async (req, res) => {
    try {
      await fn(req, res)
    } catch (err) {
      // perform your logic here...
      console.log(err.stack)
    }
  }
}

saba(handleError(async (req, res) => {
  send(res, 'ready')
}))
```

